1 SECTION 2. The amendments to ORS 320.350 by section 1 of this 2026 Act become oper-
2 ative on January 1, 2027.
3 SECTION 3. The amendments to ORS 320.350 by section 1 of this 2026 Act apply to net
4 revenue collected by units of local government before, on or after the effective date of this
5 2026 Act.
6 SECTION 4. (1)(a) A unit of local government that imposes a local transient lodging tax
7 under ORS 320.345 to 320.365 shall file a biennial report with the Legislative Revenue Officer
8 no later than September 1 of each odd-numbered year, beginning in 2027.
9 (b) Upon request by one or more cities or counties, the League of Oregon Cities or the
10 Association of Oregon Counties, respectively, may file the report on behalf of the cities or
11 counties.
12 (2) The report must include the following information with respect to total transient
13 lodging tax revenue:
14 (a) For the preceding two fiscal years:
15 (A) The tax rates imposed, setting forth separately those rates that were imposed or in-
16 creased on or before July 1, 2003, and those rates that were imposed or increased on or after
17 July 2, 2003;
18 (B) Total revenue collected;
19 (C) The amount and percentage of revenue used to fund tourism promotion, including
20 revenue expended under agreements with destination management organizations;
21 (D) The amount and percentage of revenue used to fund tourism-related facilities; and
22 (E) The amount and percentage of revenue used to fund city or county services;
23 (b) The amount of revenue held in capital reserves, with a description of its intended
24 purpose;
25 (c) Any changes to allocation methods or use definitions, including those approved by the
26 voters or unit of local government; and
27 (d) A summary of advisory board meetings or oversight actions, if applicable.
28 (3)(a) Any destination management organization or other entity receiving local transient
29 lodging tax revenue under an agreement entered into with a unit of local government shall
30 submit a biennial report to the unit of local government for inclusion in the biennial report
31 required under subsection (1) of this section.
32 (b) A report required under paragraph (a) of this subsection shall include a description
33 of:
34 (A) The uses of the local transient lodging tax revenue received under the terms of the
35 agreement, including, but not limited to, marketing and staffing;
36 (B) Performance metrics of tourism promotion, including campaigns executed and audi-
37 ences reached; and
38 (C) Compliance with the terms of the agreement and key deliverables satisfied.
39 (4) The Legislative Revenue Officer shall submit an aggregate summary of reports re-
40 ceived under subsection (1) of this section for each biennium, in the manner provided in ORS
41 192.245, to the interim committees of the Legislative Assembly related to revenue, economic
42 development and local government.
43 SECTION 5. Section 4 of this 2026 Act is repealed on January 2, 2041.
44 SECTION 6. (1) The Legislative Revenue Officer shall conduct a study of the percentage
45 requirements for allowable uses of local transient lodging tax revenue under ORS 320.350 (6),
